description:
Stop, you're killin' me!

Ever since getting turned into a vampire against his will, Gene Young has been tossed from one new nightmare to the next. First it was the ultimate shocker-discovering that he was mysteriously transformed into a beautiful teenage girl. Then it was forfeiting his old life because no one even remembered he existed. And now? Gene's stuck in multiple love triangles where everyone around him is either madly in love with him or out to kill him...or both!

Gene's only recourse is to hide his pretty face behind thick glasses, scruffy haircut, and a boy's uniform, and hope no one discovers his topsy turvy secret: that he's a boy, turned into a girl, masquerading as a boy who's really a vampire! (Whether this will fool the assassins sent by the Elders to bring back his head on a stick is anybody's guess...)
name: Vol. 5

description:
Do you have a crappy job? Poopert sure does! He works at Poop Office, an office staffed entirely by poop! Join Poopert and his co-workers for more exciting adventures in the thrilling second issue! Featuring office Chrustmas parties, a broken photocrapier machine, and Mr. Poopson's first name! Also includes deleted scenes from the cutting room floor!

Exclusively available digitally in COLOR and HIGH RESOLUTION! Includes Poop Office 12-23, Shorts 25-45, and six Poop Office deleted scenes.
By trying to help his new friend, Wendell discovers the truth about Sir Habersham's past. This issue also features short stories from the larger world of Reason for Dragons!
name: Truth and Consequences

description: Private Investigator J. Parker Wrighte is investigating the suicide of film star Pepper O'Dell for Monolith Studios. After meeting the seductive screen idol Domino Mueller, Parker escorts her to a meeting with Dr. Rome at his clinic. Here is accosted by Bill Smith,an old associate from his tenement roots. As things are turning ugly, Domino steps in calms everyone down. Then she and Parker share a romantic tryst at her estate. Parker later meets Bill at a saloon in the old neighborhood where they discuss two related suicides, the mysterious Dr. Rome and watch the alcoholic Fr. Pat take a misguided parishioner to task. Features special pencil art and thumbnail gallery.

volume.name: Retrowood: All Roads Lead To Rome

description: Sonic Super Digest is BACK and better than ever! Sonic the Hedgehog's adventures are now available in the popular digest format. You wanted new stories? You got 'em! Get ready to jump sky high as we present the adaptation of the hit Apple iOS game SONIC JUMP! Dr. Eggman's plans are always thwarted when Sonic and his pals run towards him but what happens when the devilish doctor makes his escape going straight up? Can Sonic save his little animal buddies or will he wind up crashing to the ground in embarrassment? All this (and Freedom Fighters too) as we give you more classic Sonic comics as only Sonic Super Digest can provide!

BUCKLE YOUR SEA-BELTS, BUCCANEERS, THE END BE NEAR! The thrilling high-stakes high sea adventure concludes, with the Egg o' War ready to launch, and all th' worlds in peril! It's Blaze vs. Cpt. Metal. The power of the Sol Emeralds a'beckons, as does the transformation into Burning Blaze-blimey!

name: Pirate Plunder Panic Conclusion

description: A digital only release. Chad and John find themselves face to face with their worst nightmare… a collective of human-loving, scarf-wearing vampires intent on assimilating them. Can the Suckers remain murderous creatures of the night, or will they trade their blood-lust for dark poetry and hours upon hours of brooding?
The battle with the pirates rages and Hayden finds himself in an even more dire situation as sworn enemies become uneasy allies.

Dark Cheshire and the New Mad Hatter Return! Calie and Violet's search for answers to defeat the realm of madness leads them to the site of the original "EXPERIMENT" that opened the first portal to Wonderland. But the answers they find may prove too much to bare as a startling decision is made that will change the Wonderland forever. Meanwhile, the Dark Cheshire, and the newly crowned Mad Hatters' search for Calie and Violet lead them to the foster home of the recently escaped suicide king who is attempting to learn to lead a normal life. Unfortunately, he will also learn that that is no Escape From Wonderland.

Christmas time is here... and Santa's reindeer are on strike?!! The jolly man in red calls on his trusted assistant Archie to help get things back on track in time for the biggest night of the year. Can Archie inspire everyone to work together, or will this be a present-less holiday for children all over the world? Find out in "A Christmas Story!"
name: A Christmas Story

description:
While her parents are abroad in India, Crystal "christie" Hope turns her restless, curious mind to the cases of her uncle Sherlock Holmes. That is, when she is no occupied by such hardships as dancing lessons, poetry recitations, horrid playmates, and marauding dodo birds.

Dark secrets emerge from the past of Christie's loyal maids, as well as surprising revelations about the Hope family; and Christie herself must confront her future as a noble, high-society lady.

Christie's cases in this book include:

  • The Adventure of the Solitary Cyclist
  • The Adventure of the Dying Message
name: Vol. 5

description: A traveling Inventor is rescued by a mysterious Ringmaster. Given refuge within the Circus, he builds Ardee the Robot. But an extended stay sprouts suspicions that there may be more sinister secrets afoot.

Alison Carter is a private detective. Her beat: the end of the world, or more accurately, preventing same. With an attitude of 'shoot first and the hell with the questions,' she leads a life that would drive other investigators mad, filled with monsters, demons, trolls, mad prophets, zombie detectives, technomages, machine-gun toting imps and dead boyfriends. In the first action-packed installment of this new universe, Al is given her biggest assignment ever, one that will take her into the heart of Ultimate Darkness itself. The first of a four-issue miniseries, this issue contains 30 pages of story, unbroken by advertisements.

In Ancient Greece, an 18-year-old farmhand and his twin sister embark on an epic adventure to protect their mother, and all they know and love, from Hera, the vengeful queen of the gods. Apollo is a graphic novel of classic Greek mythology, uniquely re-imagined within the H.P. Lovecraft Cthulhu Mythos universe.
name: GN

description:
The British are coming! Volume One of the British Showcase Anthology features a collection of stories from some of the best indie talent and new creators working in the British comic book industry. Excite your senses with this cover bursting collection of Horror and Sci-Fi to terrify and delight you.

Story Titles

  • Dragonfly
  • Comic COn
  • Gateway Drugs
  • Intergalactic Bank Robbing Teenage Space Aliens On the Run
  • Lycan Island
  • My Fathers Hand
  • The Pond
  • Demon Tree
  • No Vacancies
  • Tomorrow Will Be Different
  • Singularity
  • Sweet Dreams
  • Bucket Crew
  • Extraordinary Rendition
  • Capsule
  • Blood Dolls
  • Lord of the Flies
  • The Muse
  • New Luna
name: Volume One

description: BIONIC BOMBSHELL is fun Superhero romp set in ACME city where Robotics Scientist Shelly Acorn has Inherited a Super Suit and the Responsibilty of defending the City from it's more Colorful Supervillians.
name: One and Done Shot

person_credits.name: Derec Donovan
person_credits.role: writer, artist, letterer, colorist, cover, other

description: Mind-Bending Action Adventure! Really.

From actor (Lost, Vampire Diaries, and more) to environmental activist, Ian Somherhalder is someone who cares deeply about the craft of acting and the stewardship of the planet. Read the life story of the young actor who works to restore the gulf after the devastating effects of the BP disaster while balancing the demands of Hollywood stardom.

Dracula never died in Europe. His remains lie deep in the belly of Erebus, a ship ready to depart an English port. No one can explain the disappearance of sailors as they arrive in New York, a brave new world governed by anonymity. Soon word of the Vampire legend spreads and reaches England, where the fellowship of hunters gets to hear of it. And the hunt resumes.
name: GN

description: A fantasy epic about a flame trying to find its way home with the help of a stone giant and a couple of bickering birds.
The most insane game of Handball you will ever see! No words, only actions as two men compete to be the supreme lord of Handball in the silliest ways imaginable.

It all begins here! Hardcore Luchador Issue #1 sets the stage for what is sure to become your favorite new series.

The Hardcore Luchadores, El Fuego and El Muerto, are the Tag-Team Champions of the world! But what happens when they are no longer in their world and have to survive on a strange and dangerous new one?

All-Ages action and adventure abounds in Hardcore Luchador Issue #1!
Max is the least popular kid at school. He has a crush on the most popular girl in school, Candy! He has decided he's going to ask her to be his girlfriend, what do think she will say?
name: Chapter One

description: When Howard's father is stricken by an evil alien entity, Howard, Spot and Constable Smith must race to a secret government base in Antarctica to seek out the one man who can save his life: Dr. Herbert West. But the doctor has unwittingly awakened a sinister presence in the frozen wasteland that threatens to enter our world. In the end, one our heroes will be forced to Sacrifice his life to prevent the monstrosity from entering our destroying our planet.
name: TPB

volume.name: Howard Lovecraft and the Kingdom of Madness

description: Awakened from his 65 million year hibernation, the evil alien overlord Zalex is ready to resume his conquest of the universe and he's starting with the earth. Backed by his army of evil, mutated Dino-soldiers there's nothing that can stop him....nothing but Jurassic Strike Force! Don't miss the first adventures of the team in the first original series under Zenescope's Silver Dragon Books imprint.
name: Volume One

description: From the Shuster award winning creators of Looking For Group and Gutters comes the light-hearted story of the most confident man in the world. Since 2003, Least I Could Do follows the adventures of Rayne Summers, an anti-hero by any standards, as he and his friends grow up together. There are laughs, boobs, tears and sex jokes. Also one story arc got us sued by Red Bull. True story.
name: The Complete Ninth Year Collection

volume.name: Least I Could Do: I Play To Win

description: The Lil Five have to decipher clues in a race against time to unravel the secret of the Black Cave before their nefarious adversaries steal the ancient treasure hidden within...

volume.name: The Lil' Five and the Secret of the Black Cave

description: Miles, the British aristocrat, can't get his mind off Maddie, a woman he met a year ago in Australia on a business trip. He wants her so much that he ends his engagement and heads to her homeland! Meanwhile, Maddie desperately wants to have a child, but doesn't want to be tied down with a husband. All she wants is a sperm donor with brains, looks and class so she could raise the child on her own. Maddie's mind is made up... Or is it?
name: Vo. 1

description:
Have you ever wanted a duplicate of yourself? Think again. A dimensional crunch results in multiple copies of our main character popping into existence all in the same house. Horror ensues.

A 24 Hour Comic produced at Ultimate Comics Nov. 3-4 2013.

volume.name: The Many Hazards of Dimensional Hangouts

description:
"LEGEND," Part One

The Legend of Karic grows...but its legacy is both greater and darker than the noble young mouse it is said to embody. As every victory is turned against him, Karic confronts his own past and demands answers. And the mad king Icarus launches his great war against creation.

Collects MICE TEMPLAR: LEGEND #1-8.
name: Volume 4.1

description: Alisa has always been with Dylan for as long as she can remember—she gave him her first kiss as a teenager and, later, her virginity. But when Alisa finds Dylan bedding another woman, his cruel betrayal devastates her and she brings a sad end to their long-term relationship. At her worst, an accident befalls her. When Alisa wakes up, she has lost every bit of memory related to Dylan! This is the final story of a high-profile miniseries, Million-Dollar Men, which depicts the romances of self-made millionaires.
name: Vol. 1

description:
"Omniscience" is a sci-fi graphic novel. Its story is set in a hypothetical future where augmented reality has invaded our daily lives, thanks to contact lenses superimposing virtual characters into reality. One of these characters, Ingeborg, is particularly popular: she is like a second mother for generations of children, devoted and insightful. She is, however, disavowed by more and more of her subscribers - authorities suspecting her of being more harmful than beneficial to their well-being. This is what two teenagers are going to discover when they help a young fellow from their boarding school to find his parents, who abandoned him a few years earlier for an unknown reason...

The graphic novel sits halfway between dystopian novel and psychological drama. It invites the reader to reflect on the finalities of some of the social changes that we witness today, such as the virtualization of human interaction, its increasing documentation, and its use for commercial purposes.
American paratroopers probe a mysterious Nazi university. Soon they are in the fight of their lives and discover a shocking secret that could change the course of the war, and the world.
name: Fraternity of Fear

description: The first chapter in a hilarious zombie action-adventure saga, that will be sure to make you laugh, cry, and possibly thirsty. Join "The Savior" as he tries to save the world, one person at a time.

The most hard-boiled pirate detective around finds himself in a jail cell with three criminals and an agenda, but what is it he wants? Only the ensuing battle of wits will reveal his cellmates' secrets...and his own. One thing is certain: not everyone gets a happy ending.

volume.name: Pirate Eye: Iron Bars, Wretched Tales

description:
A comic book tackling the subject of teen bullying and suicide, written by Charles "Zan" Christensen and drawn by Mark Brill.

Shannon gets picked on a lot; his dad and teachers think he should just "fit in" more, but that doesn't help. So Shannon escapes into a super-powered alter-ego whenever he's in a bad situation. But will the power within be enough to save him?

In addition to the main story, the book contains bonus pages by a collection of comics industry heavyweights, including Gail Simone (WONDER WOMAN, BIRDS OF PREY), Phil Jimenez (NEW X-MEN, WONDER WOMAN), Greg Rucka (DETECTIVE COMICS, GOTHAM CENTRAL), Matthew Clark (OUTSIDERS, WONDER WOMAN), Stephen Sadowski (JSA, WARLORD OF MARS), Dan Parent (ARCHIE, KEVIN KELLER), Donna Barr (THE DESERT PEACH), Andy Mangels (GAY COMICS), Terry Blas (BRIAR HOLLOW), and Carla Speed McNeil (FINDER).

The book contains discussion questions so that the book can be used as a tool to start a conversation about issues of bullying and harassment.

Many years ago, a ship containing a very important contract sank under mysterious circumstances. Now, the shipwreck has been discovered, but the safe is nowhere to be found. Join Scrooge on this high-seas adventure as he battles both the traitor, Rockerduck, and the elements ito solve this mystery!

volume.name: Scrooge McDuck and the Mystery of the Sunken Ship

description: Inspired by the sci-fi cult films of the 1950's comes a brand new space-tastic adventure. A bunch of scientists decide to take flight to the moon and discover a race of alien women ruled by a fierce and sadistic queen.
An alcoholic school teacher is kicked out of his home by wife. In a desperate cry for help he reaches out to the school's science teacher only to discover a disturbing secret.

The Gothic horror tradition of film icon Vincent Price is revived in these twisted comic book one-shots that transplant the best of the horror genre into innovative and bizarre landscapes for a new generation of Vincent Price fans. There are four stories in this gothic graphic novel featuring the mast of horror himself! Make sure to keep the lights on when you read it!

Story Titles

  • Dracula
  • Rule To the Sky
  • In Shadows
  • The End
name: TPB

volume.name: Vincent Price: Tales From the Darkness

description: SHE'S COMING...VIOLENZIA. A mysterious girl leaves a path of bloody destruction wherever she goes. But, why? Find out in the brand-new, full-color, 50-page comic by Richard Sala...

This is where the epic adventure begins!

Meet the boys and get ready for bullies, ghosts and exploding cupcakes!

name: The Dream that Wouldn't Go Away
The Curse of the Spider Priestess

description: A special issue focusing on Raith Craulnobur as he chronicles his upbringing and training and reveals a long secret that was repressed in the lands of A'zoth. But now, he has taken the thrones of Drohm and Carahill and controls three of the most powerful relics in all of the Realm He is now the most powerful being in the land...but is this the beginning or the end?
name: The Wind Spirits

volume.name: Fist of the North Star: Blood Brothers

person_credits.name: Charles M. Schulz
person_credits.role: writer, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description: Scrooge and family star in a television rendition of the adventures of the Marco Polo family! But will this venture pay off? Follow these dynamic explorers as they strive to find the lost ark!
name: Episode One: Finding the Ark

volume.name: The Travels of Marco Polo or the Milione

description: The amazing adventures of Marco Polo continue on this episode as our heroes endure the cruelty of the desert! Scrooge's most expensive venture might take them to...the Great Wall!
name: Episode Two: Reaching the Great Wall

volume.name: The Travels of Marco Polo or the Milione

description: Mickey is pitching his new television miniseries script to media investor Scrooge McDuck. It's a dashing tale from long ago...the tale of the great Venetian Marco Polo, and his Adventures in the Far East. As beloved friend and assistant to the great Emperor of Cathay, Kublai Khan, Marco Polo and his friends are living in the lap of luxury, and enjoying every moment of their visit to the mysterious Far East. But things get complicated when Khan sends them on a dangerous mission, one that could change the future of the Kingdom...forever.
name: Episode Three: Mission to Saiang Fu

volume.name: The Travels of Marco Polo or the Milione

description: Mickey is pitching his new television miniseries script to media investor Scrooge McDuck. In this chapter, Marco Polo and his friends are exhausted. As much as they love living in the Far East, with the great Emperor of Cathay, Kublai Khan, they just want to go home. But the Khan throws a wrench into things when he offers Marco one last mission...he must escort the lovely Princess Cocachin to Persia, where she will become Queen. Complicating matters even more, Donald is in love with the Princess! And to make matters worse, Donald Duck wants to play the part of the lovestruck Marco Polo...enraging the already jealous Daisy Duck! Can Marco... and the mini-series project, survive this forbidden romance?
name: Episode Four, The Last One: The Princess Cocachin

volume.name: The Travels of Marco Polo or the Milione

description:
THE FINAL VOLUME OF THE COMPANION SERIES TO MARK WAID'S SUPERHERO EPIC! Max Damage's final test as a superhero has come - and the world will never be the same. Allegiances will be forged and broken, long-time allies will meet their end, and one beloved character will find a strength they never knew they possessed... but is it enough to save the world? Don't miss this final volume of the companion series to Mark Waid's Eisner Award-nominated series IRREDEEMABLE!

Collects Incorruptible #25-28.
name: Volume 7

description:
Are the legends of Bo, the "teddy bear" gangsta, true? And, did we just say teddy bear gangsta?!? You're about to find out-- when Bo's girls get nabbed by a rival gang boss, the fearsome plushy gangsta is forced into action!

Bo Plushy is Scarface meets Ted, with over-the-top video game style gang boss battles.

The action continues with "Kingdom of Bo" part 2!
name: Kingdom of BO Part 2

description:
Welcome to Vermintown! Disenchanted is a stunning new webcomic from writer Simon Spurrier that will be collected twice per year, following the model of Freakangels. This is the perfect chance to get in on the ground floor and be prepared to be swept into an immersive World of forgotten secrets anchored by a spectacular web site at www.disenchantedcomic.com!

Nobody gives a crap about the little people any more.

Once they were the mainstay of folklore: goblins, leprechauns, pixies and fey. But now? Dispossessed, forgotten, doubting even their own traditions, they've trickled into Vermintown: a vast and vile city of a million inch-tall malcontents. Sprawling through an abandoned subway station deep beneath London, here myth has given way to sleaze, drugs, gangland violence and interracial hatred. Vermintown is where magic went to die.

Written by Simon Spurrier (X-Men Legacy, Crossed: Wish You Were Here), with art by German Erramouspe (Night of the Living Dead), Disenchanted is an urban thriller slipping a rusty blade between the shoulders of the familiar fairytale. What do you do when nobody believes in you?

Collecting every issue ever published of one of the most beloved comic book series of all time, this over-sized graphic novel is bursting at the seams with adventure! Follow young Gully as she searches for her missing father with the help of Garrison, a legendary swordsman; Knolan, the crafty wizard; Calibretto, an outlawed Wargolem; and the notorious mercenary Red Monika! Assaulted at every turn by a cast of memorable villains, Battle Chasers is packed with over-the-top action from cover to cover! Don't miss this definitive collection, which includes never-before-seen sketches and new artwork, including a fold-out poster!
name: HC

description: After the cataclysm that devastated Ape City, Doctor Zaius, his family, Cornelius, and Marcus are tasked with the difficult and often treacherous responsibility of rebuilding civilization. But what terror lies beneath the ruins? Ancient mysteries unfold and Ape City continues to crumble while Zaius' search for answers winds its way deeper into the unknown. Collecting issues 5-8 of the critically acclaimed series.
name: Volume Two

description:
With great power comes great responsibility, but what happens with unlimited cosmic power? When a science experiment goes wrong, Peter Parker's spider-powers are enhanced to an unbelievable degree! And the timing can't be beat - because with a cabal of deadly villains unleashing unpredictable attacks on Marvel's heroes, Spider-Man will need all his newfound might just to survive! But who or what is the real force behind Spidey's cosmic empowerment? And what battle is he destined to fight? Plus: Spider-Man teams up with the Punisher, deals with the return of Venom and battles the shrunken Psycho-Man in a totally tiny adventure! Guest-starring the Hulk, Magneto, Dr. Doom, the Frightful Four and more! Collecting AMAZING SPIDER-MAN (1963) #326-333 and ANNUAL #24, SPECTACULAR SPIDER-MAN (1976) #158-160 and ANNUAL #10, and WEB OF SPIDER-MAN (1985) #59-61 and ANNUAL #6.

Note: these volumes are released in random number order, numbering is on back cover.
name: Volume 20

description: Somewhere inside Dr. Michael Morbius is a good man who just needs a second chance. NOW!, after escaping from the Raft, Morbius the Living Vampire is on the run and desperate to quell his vampiric tendencies. But will his redemption be worse than his sin? As Morbius attempts to stay under the radar, a new threat arises - and they want him dead. But after inciting a gang war, can Morbius protect the new friends who don't know his horrible secret? Then, Morbius travels to Horizon Labs determined to cure his vampirism - but comes face-to-face with the Superior Spider-Man! And when the Rose strikes - and Morbius' humanity is destroyed - will the monster within be enough to save all he once held dear? Collecting MORBIUS: THE LIVING VAMPIRE (2013) #1-9 and AMAZING SPIDER-MAN (1963) #699.1.
name: TPB

volume.name: Morbius: The Living Vampire - The Man Called Morbius

description: Caleb Monroe and Yasmin Liang bring you all-new stories of the original Avengers, as the super-spy duo face a murderous conductor, crack the case of the Suicide Town, and get into a literal race against time. Collecting issues 4-7.
name: Volume 2

volume.name: Steed and Mrs. Peel: The Secret History of Space

description: The X-Men travel to Russia for a family reunion with Colossus' parents - and his little sister Illyana, formerly the fan-favorite New Mutant known as Magik! But the villainous Soul Skinner is on the loose, and the Russian government is prepared to stop him by any means necessary. Even if that means using a little girl and shattering a family. Then: Betsy Braddock returns! But if Betsy's back, then who is Psylocke? The X-Men head for Japan in search of answers, but find themselves at odds with the Silver Samurai! And while Mr. Sinister warns Cyclops of a deadly new threat to mutants, Gambit and Rogue face a challenge of the heart. Plus: Learn the secrets of the X-Mansion in a fact-packed guidebook! Collecting X-MEN (1991) #17- 24, X-MEN: SURVIVAL GUIDE TO THE MANSION and material from MARVEL SWIMSUIT SPECIAL #2.
name: TPB

description: Because you demanded it! The X-Women get their own book, from critically acclaimed superstars Brian Wood (X-MEN, ULTIMATE X-MEN, DMZ, The Massive) and Olivier Coipel (AVX, HOUSE OF M, THOR)! An old enemy shows up at the X-Men's door, seeking asylum from an ancient evil. John Sublime is back, but he's not who we should be afraid of! Who or what is Arkea? Meanwhile, Jubilee returns home - with an orphaned baby who might hold the key to Earth's survival - or its destruction! Against a backdrop of what seems like an alien invasion and an eonsspanning war between brother and sister, Storm puts together a team to protect the child and stop a new threat that could destroy all life on the planet! Plus: Jubilee's classic first appearance! Collecting X-MEN (2013) #1-4 and UNCANNY X-MEN (1963) #244.
name: Volume 1

name: X-Men: Pianeta X

description:
Get ready to feast on another giant chapter of Seraph of the End: Vampire Reign! But this chapter focuses on the vampire world! And in Naruto, Obito's down! But right before Sasuke strikes the final blow, someone comes to his defense! Who? Plus, a special bonus chapter of One-Punch Man! All that, and more!

description:
With this month’s cover comes the last installment of The Dark-Hunters: Infinity! When Nick finally discovers what Coach Devus is plotting, as well as his weakness, can he finally take down the coach with a little help from his friends? Be sure to check out this last chapter and be on the lookout for The Dark-Hunters: Infinity, Vol. 2 heading to stores in December 2013!!

But that’s not all! In the latest chapter of The Infernal Devices, Tessa learns the truth about her parents, Will continues on his journey to save her, and Jem makes a final decision…! Meanwhile, Max and the flock are in for an icy cold surprise—but what else is new for a group of genetic experiments trying to save the world from the South Pole?! And speaking of colds, Tsugumi is down for the count in the latest chapter of Soul Eater NOT! Luckily (?) she’s got two very caring friends competing to nurse her back to health! We’ve got another chapter of Soul Eater NOT and even more in store for you in this month’s issue of Yen Plus—including some very important news! So be sure to read the editor’s letter as you dive in to the latest chapters of all your favorite series!

deck: For digital release, the issues of Faction are split up into separate issues, called singles. This is single #1 of issue #2.
description: Awakening is a postapocalyptic romp, that could be the beginning of a beautiful friendship. Saurian Age is a lesson, not just in how to dispatch a group of raptors, but how to do it in style.
name: Awakening; Saurian Era

deck: For digital release, Faction 2 was split into separate issues, called singles. This is single #2 of issue #2.
name: Ectype; A Day at the Races; Woman King

deck: Translate : Wolverine (2003) #12 , Weapon X ( 2002 ) #22 , Mystique (2003) #19 , Emma Frost (2003) #12
description: Translate : Wolverine (2003) #12 , Weapon X ( 2002 ) #22 , Mystique (2003) #19 , Emma Frost (2003) #12

"Against All Odds" featuring the popular heroine Aspen Matthews by Vince Hernandez and illustrated by Siya Oum. This unique Fathom web comic will be a special story related to the Gulf of Mexico Oil Spill, and ALL of Aspen's proceeds from sales of the web comic will be donated to the National Wildlife Federation in order to join the fight and help support wildlife affected by the oil spill.
name: Against All Odds

volume.name: Michael Turner's Fathom: Against All Odds
